threepio.documenter
Class XDocumenter

java.lang.Object
  threepio.documenter.XDocumenter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Documenter
public class XDocumenter
extends java.lang.Object
implements Documenter

XDocumenter imports an XML file to an XDoc. This is done by reading the file for tags and the strings between them, and putting them into the XDoc sequentially. The end result of the conversion is a container. It's possible that this class and others used for XML conversion can also be used for HTML conversion, but this is untested.

Author:
jhoule
See Also:
XDoc
